WEBVTT

00:02.068 --> 00:03.836
<i>♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:03.903 --> 00:05.572
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.638 --> 00:06.740
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:06.806 --> 00:08.341
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:08.408 --> 00:09.976
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:10.043 --> 00:13.780
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:13.847 --> 00:16.248
<i>♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.315 --> 00:18.952
<i>♪ Duck, dodge, push, and shove</i>
<i>is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:19.018 --> 00:21.521
<i>♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.588 --> 00:22.922
<i>♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:22.989 --> 00:24.724
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.791 --> 00:28.428
<i>♪ Loud! House! Loud! ♪</i>

00:28.495 --> 00:29.629
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.696 --> 00:30.630
{\an7}Poo-poo.

00:34.701 --> 00:37.637
[funky music]

00:42.709 --> 00:44.177
[bell rings]

00:44.244 --> 00:46.980
{\an5}Lincoln Loud in the house.

00:44.244 --> 00:46.980
Oh, yeah.

00:47.046 --> 00:49.182
L-Train pulling
into the station.

00:49.249 --> 00:52.018
{\an5}Howdy, Loudy?

00:49.249 --> 00:52.018
Saved your seat, buddy.

00:52.085 --> 00:53.453
[sighs]
Fifth grade.

00:53.520 --> 00:55.255
After half a decade
with these guys,

00:55.321 --> 00:57.590
I really feel like
I'm part of the gang.

00:57.657 --> 00:59.826
Yep, life is pretty good.

00:59.893 --> 01:01.428
Attention, class.

01:01.494 --> 01:03.530
{\an3}I'd like to introduce
our new student,

01:03.596 --> 01:05.031
Lincoln's little sister,

01:05.098 --> 01:07.233
{\an3}Lisa Loud.

01:05.098 --> 01:07.233
[gasp]

01:07.300 --> 01:08.935
{\an3}Why don't you sit
next to your brother?

01:09.002 --> 01:11.070
{\an3}Clyde, you don't mind moving,
do you?

01:11.137 --> 01:12.806
{\an1}Of course not.
[blubbers]

01:12.872 --> 01:14.441
{\an1}[line trills]
Hello, Dr Lopez.

01:14.507 --> 01:16.075
{\an1}Do you have any openings
this week?

01:16.142 --> 01:18.244
{\an1}I'm having trouble
accepting change again.

01:18.311 --> 01:20.447
{\an3}Lisa, what the heck
is going on?

01:20.513 --> 01:22.115
I asked to be
transferred here

01:22.182 --> 01:25.285
because kindergarten
is a complete waste of my time.

01:25.351 --> 01:28.555
There are two boy monkeys
and three girl monkeys.

01:28.621 --> 01:31.524
How many are there total?
Let's count together.

01:31.591 --> 01:34.427
{\an5}[all]
One monkey,
two monkeys--

01:34.494 --> 01:36.629
{\an3}Five.

01:36.696 --> 01:40.066
{\an5}[all]
Three monkeys,
four monkeys--

01:40.133 --> 01:43.236
{\an3}For the love of Pythagoras,
it's five.

01:43.303 --> 01:45.505
Lisa, you seem
a little cranky.

01:45.572 --> 01:48.641
{\an5}How about we all take a nap?

01:45.572 --> 01:48.641
[all]
Yay!

01:48.708 --> 01:51.411
No time for that.
I'm this close to synthesizing

01:51.478 --> 01:53.980
an antidote
for streptococcal pharyngitis,

01:54.047 --> 01:55.915
street name: strep throat.

01:55.982 --> 01:58.418
{\an1}You can play more later,
sweetie.

01:58.485 --> 02:00.620
Okay, kindergarten's
not challenging you,

02:00.687 --> 02:02.989
{\an3}but why do you have to come
to my class?

02:03.056 --> 02:04.457
I wanted to go straight
to med school

02:04.524 --> 02:06.493
but that dunderhead
in the principal's office

02:06.559 --> 02:09.062
said fifth grade was
the best he could offer.

02:09.127 --> 02:11.698
Fine, just try not to
rock the boat, okay?

02:11.764 --> 02:14.434
Okay, class, you should have
read up to chapter 12

02:14.501 --> 02:16.135
of your world history books.

02:16.202 --> 02:18.137
Lisa, since you're new,
I don't expect you to have--

02:18.204 --> 02:20.373
{\an7}Done.
Interesting read,

02:20.440 --> 02:23.042
{\an7}if a bit light
on indigenous cultures.

02:23.109 --> 02:25.144
Wow.
If a former kindergartener

02:25.211 --> 02:26.746
can read the whole book
this quickly,

02:26.813 --> 02:29.516
I expect all of you
to do the same...

02:29.582 --> 02:32.018
{\an5}by tomorrow.

02:29.582 --> 02:32.018
[all groan]

02:32.085 --> 02:33.920
{\an1}If you want us to retain
the information,

02:33.987 --> 02:35.822
I suggest a pop quiz.

02:35.889 --> 02:38.091
{\an5}Agreed!

02:35.889 --> 02:38.091
[all groan]

02:39.626 --> 02:43.162
Okay, class, time to present
your robotics projects.

02:43.229 --> 02:45.698
Lisa, it's okay
if you wanna sit this out.

02:45.765 --> 02:47.233
Give me a moment.

02:48.768 --> 02:50.036
Say hello to Todd.

02:50.103 --> 02:52.205
{\an1}He's fluent in over
600 languages.

02:52.272 --> 02:57.210
<i>Hola, bonjour,</i>
<i>guten tag,</i> good-bye.

02:57.277 --> 02:58.711
[laser blasts]

02:58.778 --> 03:02.115
{\an1}Oh, and he destroys
anything inferior to him.

03:02.181 --> 03:04.050
[all groan]

03:06.719 --> 03:10.123
Hey, guys,
make a little room?

03:10.189 --> 03:12.859
It's me, L-Train.
What's the problem?

03:12.926 --> 03:15.228
The problem is your sister.

03:15.295 --> 03:18.831
Look, I know Lisa's different,
but she'll grow on you.

03:18.898 --> 03:20.433
Now if I could just--

03:20.500 --> 03:23.570
{\an1}Sorry, you're sitting
over there.

03:23.636 --> 03:25.271
[Lincoln]
The sticky table?

03:28.841 --> 03:31.811
{\an3}Lincoln, enter.
I'm just drafting a proposal

03:31.878 --> 03:33.313
to eliminate recess.

03:33.379 --> 03:35.648
{\an1}That's exactly what I need
to talk to you about.

03:35.715 --> 03:37.617
{\an1}You're acting way too smart
in class.

03:37.684 --> 03:40.620
{\an1}It's annoying everyone,
and they're taking it out on me.

03:40.687 --> 03:43.222
Could you please just try
and act like an average kid?

03:43.289 --> 03:44.891
That's like asking
a sea cucumber

03:44.958 --> 03:47.727
{\an5}to act like a cephalopod.

03:44.958 --> 03:47.727
[crickets chirping]

03:47.794 --> 03:50.029
I see someone didn't do
his science homework.

03:50.096 --> 03:51.698
Lisa, please.
Thanks to you,

03:51.764 --> 03:53.967
{\an1}I've been banished
to the sticky table.

03:54.033 --> 03:55.501
Look at these pants.

03:55.568 --> 03:57.403
{\an3}I sympathise with your plight,
Lincoln,

03:57.470 --> 03:59.572
{\an3}and I suppose that
acting average

03:59.639 --> 04:02.709
could be a fascinating
sociological challenge.

04:02.775 --> 04:03.876
Okay, I'll do it.

04:03.943 --> 04:06.412
{\an1}Thank you,
you're the best.

04:06.479 --> 04:09.248
Grab my saw,
I'm stuck to your pants.

04:09.315 --> 04:11.250
[bell rings]

04:11.317 --> 04:14.554
{\an1}Greetings, classmates!
It's me, Lisa.

04:14.621 --> 04:17.557
{\an5}Whoa, you look so average.

04:14.621 --> 04:17.557
{\an1}Thank you.

04:17.624 --> 04:19.659
I created an algorithm
based on the traits

04:19.726 --> 04:22.795
{\an5}of typical fifth graders,
and reinvented myself
accordingly.

04:22.862 --> 04:24.063
Don't you need your glasses?

04:24.130 --> 04:26.833
Pshaw.
I took care of that.

04:26.899 --> 04:29.836
[thrashing rock music]

04:29.902 --> 04:32.672
♪♪

04:32.739 --> 04:35.308
{\an8}Physical appearance
was the easy part.

04:35.375 --> 04:38.411
{\an7}Acting average
is a far greater challenge,

04:38.478 --> 04:40.913
{\an7}so I invented this baby
to keep me honest.

04:40.980 --> 04:42.181
What does it do?

04:42.248 --> 04:43.416
Okay, class,

04:43.483 --> 04:45.918
who can recite
the Gettysburg Address?

04:45.985 --> 04:47.687
{\an8}Four score and--
[collar buzzes]

04:47.754 --> 04:49.188
{\an7}[yells]
I mean,

04:49.255 --> 04:51.758
{\an7}85 Elm Street.
Get it?

04:51.824 --> 04:54.594
[laughter]

04:54.661 --> 04:58.264
Who knows the most common gas
in the Earth's atmosphere?

04:58.331 --> 04:59.999
{\an7}Nitrogen.
Gah!

05:00.066 --> 05:01.734
{\an8}I mean, methane!

05:01.801 --> 05:03.269
{\an7}[toots]
Get it?

05:03.336 --> 05:06.172
[laughter]

05:06.239 --> 05:08.174
Time for a pop quiz,
everyone.

05:08.241 --> 05:10.143
{\an5}[all groan]

05:08.241 --> 05:10.143
[device beeps]

05:10.209 --> 05:13.179
Pop quizzes stink.

05:13.246 --> 05:14.747
[laser blast]

05:14.814 --> 05:17.750
I reprogrammed Todd
to be average too.

05:17.817 --> 05:19.886
[all cheering]

05:19.952 --> 05:22.055
{\an1}Okay,
moment of truth.

05:22.121 --> 05:23.690
Hey, guys,
mind if we sit down?

05:23.756 --> 05:25.925
{\an1}Lincoln and his
super cool sister?

05:25.992 --> 05:28.761
{\an1}Sh'yeah.
Slide down, guys.

05:28.828 --> 05:31.931
This cafeteria fare
has no nutritional value,

05:31.998 --> 05:35.268
and so I would like to make
a proposal.

05:35.334 --> 05:37.603
{\an3}Food fight!

05:39.105 --> 05:43.342
Yes, Principal Huggins,
it will not happen again, sir.

05:43.409 --> 05:44.877
Or will it?

05:44.944 --> 05:46.579
[all] Ooh!

05:46.646 --> 05:50.249
{\an5}Hilarious.

05:46.646 --> 05:50.249
Nice one, L-Dawg.

05:50.316 --> 05:51.818
{\an3}You sure burned
his biscuits.

05:51.884 --> 05:54.687
{\an1}Lisa, I think you're
officially part of the gang.

05:54.754 --> 05:57.757
{\an5}[woman]
McBride, Principal Huggins
will see you next.

05:57.824 --> 05:59.292
He doesn't scare me.

06:00.993 --> 06:02.195
[snaps fingers]

06:02.261 --> 06:03.663
{\an1}[sobs]
I'm so sorry.

06:03.730 --> 06:06.632
{\an1}Please, don't put this
on my record.

06:08.267 --> 06:09.902
[glass breaking]

06:12.205 --> 06:13.906
Lisa, what's going on?

06:13.973 --> 06:15.141
Meh, just getting rid of

06:15.208 --> 06:16.642
all this stupid old
science stuff.

06:16.709 --> 06:18.845
{\an1}You don't have to go
that far.

06:18.911 --> 06:20.379
{\an3}Oh, I do.
Lincoln,

06:20.446 --> 06:22.815
{\an3}you have opened
my surgically-corrected eyes.

06:22.882 --> 06:25.852
{\an3}Being part of the gang is
way more fun than being smart.

06:25.918 --> 06:29.288
Say hello
to the new Lisa Loud.

06:29.355 --> 06:31.491
Street name: L-Dawg.

06:31.557 --> 06:33.993
Have you heard of
Boys Will Be Boys?

06:34.060 --> 06:35.561
[pop music]

06:35.628 --> 06:37.563
{\an8}They're not quite
Stravinsky, but--

06:37.630 --> 06:40.500
{\an7}Gah!
I mean, they're so cute.

06:40.566 --> 06:43.469
{\an1}Dude, you gotta help me
cram for my test tomorrow.

06:43.536 --> 06:45.371
{\an8}Sorry, I'm out of
the tutoring game.

06:45.438 --> 06:47.173
{\an8}Bogus, since when?

06:47.240 --> 06:50.009
{\an7}Since Lincoln showed me
the joys of being average.

06:50.076 --> 06:52.445
{\an1}[growls]

06:52.512 --> 06:54.514
[all gagging and spitting]

06:54.580 --> 06:56.849
{\an5}[indistinct clamouring]

06:54.580 --> 06:56.849
This is so disgusting.

06:56.916 --> 06:59.585
{\an1}It's not my fault!
The recipe is in metric,

06:59.652 --> 07:02.155
{\an1}and Lisa usually helps me
with the conversions.

07:02.221 --> 07:04.757
{\an3}Thanks to Lincoln,
I'm out of the conversion game,

07:04.824 --> 07:06.926
{\an3}except for converting
beans to methane.

07:06.993 --> 07:08.327
{\an3}[toots]

07:08.394 --> 07:10.196
[all growling]

07:10.263 --> 07:12.031
{\an1}[gulps]

07:12.098 --> 07:14.834
{\an5}[DJ]
<i>I've got free passes</i>
<i>to the Royal Woods Day Spa</i>

07:14.901 --> 07:16.369
<i>for the first caller</i>
<i>who can name all three</i>

07:16.435 --> 07:18.671
<i>classifications of rocks.</i>

07:18.738 --> 07:21.440
{\an1}Eee!

07:21.507 --> 07:23.242
{\an1}Lisa,
tell him the answer!

07:23.309 --> 07:25.845
{\an1}Hard rock, soft rock,
and indie.

07:25.912 --> 07:27.446
<i>Uh...no.</i>

07:27.513 --> 07:30.650
<i>You lose, baby.</i>

07:30.716 --> 07:32.485
What?
Thanks to Lincoln,

07:32.552 --> 07:35.588
I'm out of the geology game.

07:36.923 --> 07:38.491
[phone rings,
receiver picks up]

07:38.558 --> 07:40.226
Oh, hi, Dad.
You've been waiting

07:40.293 --> 07:42.195
at the train station
for an hour?

07:42.261 --> 07:44.330
Oh, my gosh,
I am so sorry.

07:44.397 --> 07:46.399
Just stay put,
I'll be right there.

07:46.465 --> 07:48.835
Aww, poor Pop-Pop.
What happened?

07:48.901 --> 07:51.337
Well, usually
when Pop-Pop's on a train

07:51.404 --> 07:52.705
headed east
going 80 miles an hour,

07:52.772 --> 07:54.941
and he has 230 miles
to his destination,

07:55.007 --> 07:57.043
Lisa can tell me
exactly when he'll arrive.

07:57.109 --> 07:59.846
{\an1}What can I say?
I'm out of the algebra game.

07:59.912 --> 08:01.914
Right, Lincoln?

08:01.981 --> 08:03.649
[gulps]

08:03.716 --> 08:06.319
{\an1}Oh, Lisa,
thank goodness you're here.

08:06.385 --> 08:08.020
We need the antidote
you were working on.

08:08.087 --> 08:11.157
{\an8}Sorry, Ms. S, I'm out of
the disease control game.

08:11.224 --> 08:14.327
{\an8}My big brother here showed me
how lame and annoying it is

08:14.393 --> 08:15.461
{\an8}to be an egghead.

08:15.528 --> 08:18.865
And I am out of here.

08:18.931 --> 08:20.633
Way to go, buster.

08:20.700 --> 08:22.435
Now all my kids have
strep throat.

08:22.501 --> 08:24.270
I'm sorry,
but I didn't have a choice.

08:24.337 --> 08:27.406
If she kept acting like a brain,
I was gonna be out of the gang.

08:27.473 --> 08:31.410
{\an1}Well, as long as it's
for a good reason.

08:31.477 --> 08:34.447
{\an3}I was gonna have to sit
at the stinky table.

08:34.513 --> 08:37.149
[all cheering]

08:37.216 --> 08:40.253
{\an3}Lisa, you have to go back
to being smart.

08:40.318 --> 08:42.520
{\an1}What?
And give up all this?

08:42.587 --> 08:45.324
[all]
Lisa! Lisa! Lisa!

08:45.391 --> 08:48.527
Not likely.

08:48.594 --> 08:51.564
{\an5}Thanks, L-Dawg.

08:48.594 --> 08:51.564
{\an3}Ay!

08:51.631 --> 08:53.032
Lisa, listen to me.

08:53.099 --> 08:55.134
Any half-wit can be
a part of the gang.

08:55.201 --> 08:56.836
No offense, Zach.

08:56.903 --> 08:59.372
{\an3}But no one else I know
can heal sick people

08:59.438 --> 09:00.840
{\an3}and save Dad's cooking,
and figure out

09:00.907 --> 09:02.942
{\an3}what time Pop-pop's train
is arriving.

09:03.009 --> 09:06.279
What I'm trying to say is,
the world needs smart Lisa.

09:06.345 --> 09:07.880
{\an1}Flattering words,
big brother,

09:07.947 --> 09:09.682
but I already bought
this leather jacket.

09:09.749 --> 09:11.284
I'll pay you back for it.

09:11.350 --> 09:12.985
Just go finish the antidote,
please.

09:13.052 --> 09:14.921
What about the gang,
and being part of it?

09:14.987 --> 09:16.622
I'd rather be
the one to suffer

09:16.689 --> 09:18.557
than a classroom full of kids
with strep throat.

09:18.624 --> 09:20.860
Man, I can't have that
on my conscience.

09:20.927 --> 09:23.529
{\an1}Okay, but if I go back
to being smart Lisa,

09:23.596 --> 09:25.598
{\an1}you're getting
the whole package,

09:25.665 --> 09:27.833
i.e. unabashed superiority

09:27.900 --> 09:30.069
{\an1}and zero tolerance
for ignoramuses.

09:30.136 --> 09:33.072
{\an1}It'll probably be back
to the sticky table for you.

09:33.139 --> 09:35.207
{\an3}That's a chance
I'm willing to take.

09:35.274 --> 09:36.809
{\an1}You're a good man,
Lincoln Loud.

09:36.876 --> 09:39.679
{\an1}As Socrates once quipped...
[collar buzzes]

09:39.745 --> 09:43.049
{\an7}Yak!
Ugh, to heck with this thing.

09:43.115 --> 09:46.085
[alarm beeping]

09:48.688 --> 09:51.791
[all whining]

09:51.857 --> 09:53.726
Line up.
No pushing.

09:53.793 --> 09:55.795
There's plenty for everyone.

09:57.430 --> 09:59.165
So how'd it go this morning?

09:59.231 --> 10:00.599
We lost one.

10:00.666 --> 10:03.035
{\an3}I'm kidding, it went fine.
All cured.

10:03.102 --> 10:04.370
Good job.

10:04.437 --> 10:07.106
{\an3}Lunch for two
at the sticky table?

10:07.173 --> 10:08.307
[snoring]

10:08.374 --> 10:10.710
L-Train and L-Dawg!
Park it!

10:10.776 --> 10:12.778
{\an5}Really?

10:10.776 --> 10:12.778
I must give you fair warning,

10:12.845 --> 10:15.147
{\an1}I have reverted
to my previous incarnation.

10:15.214 --> 10:16.148
[crickets chirping]

10:16.215 --> 10:17.383
Smart Lisa's back.

10:17.450 --> 10:19.218
Smart Lisa's fine by me.

10:19.285 --> 10:21.988
My little sissy's in that
there kindergarten class.

10:22.054 --> 10:24.724
Yeah, and that virus
could've spread to all of us.

10:24.790 --> 10:27.526
I can't get strep.
I've got a date on Friday.

10:27.593 --> 10:30.696
We're sorry
we treated you badly before.

10:30.763 --> 10:32.064
Our class sure is lucky

10:32.131 --> 10:34.266
{\an3}to have someone with smarts
like yours.

10:34.333 --> 10:36.802
Thanks for your support, guys,
but you don't have to worry.

10:36.869 --> 10:38.637
I'm going back
to kindergarten.

10:38.704 --> 10:41.107
So I can have my seat back?
Hello? Dr Lopez?

10:41.173 --> 10:43.709
I don't need that appointment
after all.

10:43.776 --> 10:45.411
{\an1}What about wanting
a challenge?

10:45.478 --> 10:47.646
{\an3}Meh,
kindergarten, fifth grade,

10:47.713 --> 10:49.648
it's all a snooze fest to me.

10:49.715 --> 10:52.084
I'm gonna pursue my own
studies either way,

10:52.151 --> 10:55.254
and kindergarten does have
one major advantage.

10:55.321 --> 10:58.858
Okay, boys and girls,
naptime.

10:58.924 --> 11:02.128
Now. Lisa, I know you're
not gonna want a nap, but--

11:02.194 --> 11:03.529
Are you kidding?

11:03.596 --> 11:05.865
After the day I've had,
I am bushed.

11:05.931 --> 11:08.234
Oh, and by the way, Ms. S,
if you attempt to wake me up

11:08.300 --> 11:11.070
before my required 45 minutes
of REM sleep,

11:11.137 --> 11:14.407
you'll have to answer
to Todd.

11:14.473 --> 11:17.610
Namaste, Ms Shrinivas.

11:22.314 --> 11:25.451
[upbeat rock music]

11:31.457 --> 11:33.893
Okay, kids,
steady as she goes.

11:33.959 --> 11:35.961
[all grunting]

11:36.028 --> 11:38.364
{\an3}Lola, you are
not in a parade.

11:38.431 --> 11:40.966
{\an3}Get down here
and help us push.

11:41.033 --> 11:42.701
{\an8}Mom,
this is the third time

11:42.768 --> 11:44.770
{\an8}Vanzilla's broken down
this week.

11:44.837 --> 11:47.206
{\an8}Don't you think it might be time
for a new car?

11:47.273 --> 11:48.641
I would love a new car, guys.

11:48.707 --> 11:50.409
It's your dad
who won't go for it.

11:50.476 --> 11:53.779
Vanzilla was his father's van,
and his grandfather's.

11:53.846 --> 11:56.348
Someday, he hopes to
pass it on to you, Lincoln.

11:56.415 --> 11:59.452
[scattered laughter]

11:56.415 --> 11:59.452
You're stuck with it.

12:01.720 --> 12:04.690
[all grunting]

12:05.658 --> 12:07.093
Thanks for the assist, kids.

12:07.159 --> 12:08.327
Uh, after dinner, uh,

12:08.394 --> 12:10.329
{\an1}I'll need a push
to ceramics class.

12:10.396 --> 12:11.397
[all groan]

12:11.464 --> 12:12.731
There's got to be some way

12:12.798 --> 12:14.633
{\an3}we can convince Dad
to get a new car.

12:14.700 --> 12:15.868
{\an8}You heard Mom.

12:15.935 --> 12:18.104
{\an8}All our arguments
are just going to stall.

12:18.170 --> 12:19.772
{\an8}[laughs]
Get it?

12:19.839 --> 12:23.242
Unless we try
the subliminal approach.

12:23.309 --> 12:25.411
[all]
Mm-hmm.

12:25.478 --> 12:26.812
Wait,
where's Lola?

12:26.879 --> 12:29.315
I got knocked off
by a tree branch

12:29.381 --> 12:30.816
{\an8}three blocks back!

12:30.883 --> 12:32.952
{\an8}Thanks for noticing!

12:35.421 --> 12:36.689
{\an8}Here you go, Dad.

12:36.755 --> 12:40.392
{\an8}We made you blueberry
brand-new-van cakes.

12:40.459 --> 12:41.961
[gasps]
[chomping]

12:42.027 --> 12:46.031
{\an8}Is that a new shirt, Dad?
You look van-tastic in it.

12:46.098 --> 12:48.100
Yeah, Dad,
you da van!

12:48.167 --> 12:49.468
Thanks, girls.
Whoops,

12:49.535 --> 12:52.972
got a little hood ornament
on your face.

12:53.038 --> 12:54.306
[whistling]

12:54.373 --> 12:56.642
{\an1}Dad, can you help me
with this math problem?

12:56.709 --> 13:01.013
{\an1}If Mr Cloud's van stalls out
ten miles from his office,

13:01.080 --> 13:04.950
how late will Mr Cloud be
for his important meeting?

13:05.017 --> 13:07.520
Well, based on my experience
from last Tuesday,

13:07.586 --> 13:10.523
I'd say about three hours,
and boy is he gonna stink.

13:10.589 --> 13:13.159
{\an5}Thanks, Dad.

13:10.589 --> 13:13.159
No problem, sweetie.

13:13.225 --> 13:14.393
[resumes whistling]

13:17.897 --> 13:19.598
[sniffing]

13:19.665 --> 13:22.601
Whoa Nelly!
What is that glorious smell?

13:22.668 --> 13:25.905
It's like warm bread, roses,
and puppies all rolled into one.

13:25.971 --> 13:27.806
{\an8}Just my latest experiment.

13:27.873 --> 13:32.378
{\an7}I've recreated the intoxicating
new car smell.

13:32.444 --> 13:34.146
Wait,
new cars smell like this?

13:34.213 --> 13:35.514
I had no idea.

13:35.581 --> 13:37.316
I don't know
what's come over me,

13:37.383 --> 13:40.352
but I suddenly think it's time
the Louds get a new minivan!

13:40.419 --> 13:42.555
[all cheering]

13:42.621 --> 13:44.790
Lola and I've been working
on a new song.

13:44.857 --> 13:47.293
{\an1}It's called
"Happiness Is A New Van."

13:47.359 --> 13:48.928
{\an1}Can it.
He already said yes.

13:48.994 --> 13:52.164
{\an3}We've been practicing
for four hours!

13:52.231 --> 13:54.366
{\an3}Sit down!

13:54.433 --> 13:57.803
{\an3}And a one, a two,
a one, two, three, four!

13:57.870 --> 14:01.106
[car honks]

14:01.173 --> 14:04.143
[all] Whoa!

14:04.210 --> 14:05.778
Ain't she a beaut?

14:05.844 --> 14:08.314
I fell in love the minute
I took her for a test drive.

14:08.380 --> 14:09.348
Check this out.

14:09.415 --> 14:10.549
[beeps]

14:13.018 --> 14:15.254
[all]
Yay! Oh!

14:15.321 --> 14:16.956
Da-da-da-da-da-da,
not so fast.

14:17.022 --> 14:19.725
This van is brand new
and I wanna keep it that way.

14:19.792 --> 14:23.095
Shoes off! From now on
you'll wear these booties.

14:23.162 --> 14:24.663
Now, line up for inspection.

14:26.699 --> 14:28.934
Uh-huh, so no history
of flaking skin,

14:29.001 --> 14:31.370
projectile vomiting,
or leaky bowel syndrome.

14:31.437 --> 14:33.572
You may enter.

14:33.639 --> 14:36.442
{\an3}Okay, gang,
let's take her for a ride.

14:36.508 --> 14:37.876
[engine turns over]

14:38.944 --> 14:40.212
[gear shifts]

14:40.279 --> 14:42.081
Everybody out.
Don't smudge the door handles.

14:42.147 --> 14:43.716
[all clamouring]

14:43.782 --> 14:46.719
{\an3}Now, guys, we don't wanna rack
up the mileage on Veronica.

14:46.785 --> 14:48.420
{\an5}Who?

14:46.785 --> 14:48.420
Oh, that's the name

14:48.487 --> 14:50.389
I gave my little baby.

14:50.456 --> 14:52.024
Now everybody out.

14:53.993 --> 14:56.962
{\an1}Dad, can I borrow, um,
Veronica tomorrow?

14:57.029 --> 15:00.566
[laughs]
Oh, wait, you're serious.

15:00.633 --> 15:02.167
Oh, sorry, honey,
nobody drives her but me.

15:02.234 --> 15:04.270
And me, of course.

15:04.336 --> 15:06.238
[laughs]

15:06.305 --> 15:08.007
Oh, wait, you're serious too?

15:09.475 --> 15:12.244
I can't believe Dad won't
let you drive the new van.

15:12.311 --> 15:14.446
{\an3}How are we supposed to get
to the mall and junk?

15:14.513 --> 15:16.081
I have a plan.

15:16.148 --> 15:17.383
[piped music playing]

15:17.449 --> 15:19.852
Hello, ladies,
I'm Steve.

15:19.918 --> 15:21.153
You interested in this beauty?

15:21.220 --> 15:23.055
Very interested, Steve.

15:23.122 --> 15:25.758
{\an1}But we'll need to take it
for a test drive.

15:25.824 --> 15:27.326
Sure.

15:27.393 --> 15:29.028
[pop music]

15:29.094 --> 15:30.496
Wait, did you say "test"?

15:30.562 --> 15:32.798
Lori, I didn't study.

15:32.865 --> 15:36.135
♪♪

15:36.201 --> 15:38.270
Dad, what are you wearing?

15:38.337 --> 15:39.605
It's a beaded vest!

15:39.672 --> 15:42.241
I got his and hers
for me and Veronica.

15:42.308 --> 15:45.944
{\an1}Uh, wow,
that's---uh, wow.

15:46.011 --> 15:48.881
{\an5}Listen, can I get a ride?

15:46.011 --> 15:48.881
No can do, son.

15:48.947 --> 15:51.884
Veronica and I have
a very special outing planned.

15:51.950 --> 15:53.585
[bird chirping]

15:53.652 --> 15:56.855
Don't even think about it, pal.

15:56.922 --> 15:59.258
{\an8}Hi, I'll take three
double bacon cheeseburgers

15:59.325 --> 16:00.826
{\an8}and three drinks.

16:02.394 --> 16:03.629
Girls, getting fast food

16:03.696 --> 16:05.497
is not usually
part of the test drive.

16:05.564 --> 16:08.967
{\an3}Duh, we gotta
test the cup holders.

16:09.034 --> 16:12.371
{\an1}And we got you
a double bacon cheeseburger.

16:12.438 --> 16:13.639
Oh.

16:13.706 --> 16:16.642
I'm vegan, but what the heck.
[chomps]

16:16.709 --> 16:19.978
{\an3}Get this, my wife actually
wanted to take Veronica

16:20.045 --> 16:21.313
grocery shopping.

16:21.380 --> 16:25.584
{\an3}I mean, what if her dang
protein shakes spilled, huh?

16:25.651 --> 16:26.919
I'd never forgive myself.

16:26.985 --> 16:29.655
Ah, I never let my family
in Sophia.

16:29.722 --> 16:31.757
Gotta protect her fine
Italian leather.

16:31.824 --> 16:33.559
Isn't that right,<i> bellissima?</i>

16:33.625 --> 16:36.395
[car honks]
Whoa, check out Kotaro.

16:36.462 --> 16:37.730
What's he driving?

16:37.796 --> 16:40.699
{\an1}Gentlemen of the Royal Woods
minivan society,

16:40.766 --> 16:43.302
allow me to present Marilyn.

16:43.369 --> 16:45.404
Va-va-voo!

16:45.471 --> 16:47.239
{\an5}[Lincoln]
Okay, we all know
why we're here.

16:47.306 --> 16:49.675
Dad is out of control
with the new van.

16:49.742 --> 16:52.878
Yeah, it's almost enough
to make you miss Vanzilla.

16:52.945 --> 16:54.179
She was a hunk of junk,

16:54.246 --> 16:56.048
but at least
we could be ourselves.

16:56.115 --> 16:57.950
That's it, then.
We gotta convince Dad

16:58.016 --> 17:00.786
to trade in Veronica,
and get Vanzilla back.

17:00.853 --> 17:02.321
{\an8}Easier said than done.

17:02.388 --> 17:04.089
[exhales deeply]

17:04.156 --> 17:06.425
Veronica,
will you accept this key ring

17:06.492 --> 17:08.060
as a symbol of my love?

17:08.127 --> 17:09.461
Oh, for Pete's sake.

17:09.528 --> 17:12.164
Looks like we're gonna have
to go subliminal again.

17:12.231 --> 17:14.199
[all]
Mm-hmm.

17:15.334 --> 17:16.667
Um, I don't understand

17:16.734 --> 17:18.303
{\an3}how shopping is part
of the test drive.

17:18.369 --> 17:21.373
{\an1}Duh, we need to see how many
bags the trunk can hold.

17:21.440 --> 17:23.942
{\an6}But--

17:21.440 --> 17:23.942
{\an1}And look what
I found on sale.

17:24.009 --> 17:26.678
{\an1}It really brings out
your eyes.

17:28.747 --> 17:30.582
{\an7}Hey, Dad,
we made pizz-zilla,

17:30.649 --> 17:32.551
{\an8}pizza shaped like Vanzilla.

17:32.618 --> 17:36.088
{\an1}Brings back some memories,
doesn't it?

17:36.155 --> 17:37.523
It sure does.

17:37.589 --> 17:40.359
{\an3}Everything's fallen off of it
just like Vanzilla.

17:40.426 --> 17:41.360
{\an3}[laughs]

17:41.427 --> 17:44.163
Glad that heap's gone.

17:44.229 --> 17:45.564
I'm off to work, dear.

17:45.631 --> 17:48.333
{\an1}I know you don't trust me
to drive Veronica.

17:48.400 --> 17:50.202
{\an1}So from now on
I'll be carpooling

17:50.269 --> 17:52.337
with my co-worker, Brandon.

17:52.404 --> 17:53.605
You know, the one who just won

17:53.672 --> 17:56.241
the Mr Hunky Royal Woods
contest?

17:56.308 --> 17:58.210
[tyres screech, car honks]

17:58.277 --> 17:59.411
[lively music playing]

17:59.478 --> 18:01.013
Uh-huh,
sure, honey.

18:01.079 --> 18:04.483
Smile, Veronica.
This is going on our blog!

18:04.550 --> 18:06.218
[camera shutter clicks]

18:06.285 --> 18:07.486
Ugh.

18:07.553 --> 18:09.721
♪ ♪

18:09.788 --> 18:12.825
You can put your shirt
back on now, Brandon.

18:13.926 --> 18:16.195
{\an3}We're going to have to
up our game.

18:16.261 --> 18:17.463
[drill whirring]

18:17.529 --> 18:19.498
Okay, maybe we could do
a tour around the block,

18:19.565 --> 18:20.566
and then-- [gasps]

18:20.632 --> 18:23.735
My baby!
She's been mugged!

18:23.802 --> 18:25.437
Wow, sorry, Dad.

18:25.504 --> 18:27.272
But maybe there's a lesson here.

18:27.339 --> 18:30.242
We just can't have a car
this nice in our driveway.

18:30.309 --> 18:32.845
You're right, son.
Everybody clean out the garage.

18:32.911 --> 18:35.280
You'll be safe in there,
lambkins.

18:35.347 --> 18:37.516
Chop-chop! We need to get
Veronica in a safe place

18:37.583 --> 18:38.650
before sundown.

18:38.717 --> 18:40.953
[all groan]

18:41.019 --> 18:44.289
Well, that bit it hard.
Let's face it, dudes,

18:44.356 --> 18:47.459
{\an1}we're never gonna trick daddy-o
into getting Vanzilla back.

18:47.526 --> 18:49.461
{\an3}[gasps]
Get Vanzilla back?

18:49.528 --> 18:51.630
{\an3}What are you talking about?
Don't you like Veronica?

18:51.697 --> 18:52.865
She's fine.

18:52.931 --> 18:55.300
The problem is, well, you.

18:55.367 --> 18:57.936
Yeah, you've turned into
a total meanie,

18:58.003 --> 19:00.772
and frankly,
a bit of a weirdo.

19:00.839 --> 19:03.075
{\an5}That is unfair.

19:00.839 --> 19:03.075
No, it's not, Dad.

19:03.141 --> 19:05.177
You made me walk
all the way home from school.

19:05.244 --> 19:07.613
I was very clear
about the no-sneezing policy.

19:07.679 --> 19:10.249
{\an1}And I do not appreciate
being singled out

19:10.315 --> 19:11.817
to wear this saliva shield.

19:11.884 --> 19:13.485
I see what's happening here.

19:13.552 --> 19:16.922
You can't stand to see how happy
Veronica and I are together,

19:16.989 --> 19:18.557
so you wanna rip us apart!

19:18.624 --> 19:22.127
For shame, family,
for shame!

19:22.194 --> 19:24.696
And they called me a meanie
and a weirdo.

19:24.763 --> 19:27.866
Meanie? Check.
I have heard that one too.

19:27.933 --> 19:30.202
Yep.
Hm, weirdo? Been there.

19:30.269 --> 19:33.338
{\an1}You gotta shrug it off, Lynn.
Families just don't get it.

19:33.405 --> 19:36.108
Yeah, stand firm
on that sneeze policy.

19:36.174 --> 19:38.610
Hey, kids, who's up
for some Burpin' Burger?

19:38.677 --> 19:42.080
I'll take five burpin' burgers
with all the stuffings,

19:42.147 --> 19:43.815
and make sure that sauce
is dripping.

19:43.882 --> 19:47.319
{\an5}You're the best, Dad!

19:43.882 --> 19:47.319
We love you!

19:47.386 --> 19:48.754
[sighs]

19:48.820 --> 19:50.856
I remember
when my kids loved me.

19:50.923 --> 19:52.691
{\an3}Me too.
In my old van,

19:52.758 --> 19:54.693
{\an3}the kids used to have
squirt gun fights,

19:54.760 --> 19:55.694
and I'd just laugh.

19:55.761 --> 19:57.162
Yeah.
In my old heap,

19:57.229 --> 20:00.332
the dog gave birth
right there in the backseat.

20:00.399 --> 20:01.767
It was the cutest.

20:01.833 --> 20:03.235
Ah, to heck with it.

20:03.302 --> 20:06.071
{\an1}I'm going to trade in Olivia
and get my old van back.

20:06.138 --> 20:07.472
{\an6}Me too.

20:06.138 --> 20:07.472
[car doors closing]

20:07.539 --> 20:09.875
{\an1}Me too.
Farewell, Marilyn.

20:09.942 --> 20:12.311
{\an1}We'll always have
that first oil change.

20:12.377 --> 20:14.947
You guys are nuts.
You're gonna regret this.

20:15.013 --> 20:18.850
{\an4}[girl]
Daddy, who's that sad,
lonely man in the beaded vest?

20:18.917 --> 20:20.852
[father]
Stay away from him, kids.

20:20.919 --> 20:24.122
[sombre music]

20:24.189 --> 20:25.357
[sighs]

20:25.424 --> 20:26.625
[horn honking]

20:26.692 --> 20:28.760
Family?
I'm sorry!

20:28.827 --> 20:31.763
You were right.
Who wants to get Vanzilla back?

20:31.830 --> 20:34.333
[all cheering]

20:34.399 --> 20:36.034
But we don't have
our booties.

20:36.101 --> 20:37.736
No, I don't care anymore.

20:37.803 --> 20:40.572
Just get your beautiful
muddy feet in here.

20:40.639 --> 20:41.873
[all cheering]

20:41.940 --> 20:44.776
[exciting music]

20:44.843 --> 20:46.244
Hi,
I wanna return this van.

20:46.311 --> 20:48.814
It just didn't work out.
All right, sir.

20:48.880 --> 20:51.516
{\an3}And now I'd like to buy back
my old van.

20:51.583 --> 20:53.719
{\an1}No can do.
Just sold it for scrap

20:53.785 --> 20:55.120
{\an5}to the junkyard.

20:53.785 --> 20:55.120
[gasps]

20:55.187 --> 20:57.155
[all]
<i>♪ Ooh, girl, if I could ♪</i>

20:57.222 --> 20:59.191
<i>♪ Ooh, girl,</i>
<i>give you the ♪</i>

20:59.257 --> 21:00.726
<i>♪ Ooh, girl,</i>
<i>we're all girls ♪</i>

21:00.792 --> 21:03.795
We need to take this car
out for a test drive right now.

21:03.862 --> 21:05.464
{\an3}Dad, I think
Steve may have had enough

21:05.530 --> 21:06.865
test driving for one day.

21:06.932 --> 21:09.267
Are you kidding?
This was amazing!

21:09.334 --> 21:12.170
My nail beds have literally
never looked this good.

21:12.237 --> 21:14.940
What ever you guys wanna do,
I'm in.

21:15.007 --> 21:16.642
[all]
Whoo!

21:16.708 --> 21:18.710
♪♪

21:18.777 --> 21:21.046
[all calling for Vanzilla]

21:21.113 --> 21:22.648
Honk if you can hear me!

21:22.714 --> 21:25.250
{\an5}[all calling for Vanzilla]

21:22.714 --> 21:25.250
Come on, baby, where are ya?

21:25.317 --> 21:27.119
{\an8}There she is.

21:27.185 --> 21:28.387
♪♪

21:28.453 --> 21:29.388
[all]
No!

21:29.454 --> 21:30.856
[alarm beeping]

21:30.922 --> 21:33.191
Dad, bead me.

21:33.258 --> 21:36.461
♪♪

21:36.528 --> 21:38.864
[electricity sparking]

21:38.930 --> 21:40.465
I wanna buy this van.

21:40.532 --> 21:42.434
Seriously, this hunk of junk?

21:42.501 --> 21:46.138
She's not a hunk of junk.
She's family.

21:46.204 --> 21:47.372
[thud]

21:47.439 --> 21:49.508
Thanks for giving up
Veronica, dear.

21:49.574 --> 21:51.576
I know it was a big sacrifice.

21:51.643 --> 21:53.078
[scoffs]
Veronica who?

21:53.145 --> 21:54.746
{\an4}Aww.

21:53.145 --> 21:54.746
[both laugh]

21:54.813 --> 21:57.849
I'm just glad we can all be
together in Vanzilla again.

21:57.916 --> 21:59.184
We are too!

21:59.251 --> 22:02.454
{\an9}Even if we're not actually
in Vanzilla.

22:02.521 --> 22:03.722
[all grunting]

22:03.789 --> 22:05.824
<i>♪ Ooh, girl, if I could ♪</i>

22:10.696 --> 22:12.130
{\an8}<i>♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:12.197 --> 22:13.999
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:14.066 --> 22:16.902
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:16.968 --> 22:19.304
{\an8}<i>♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:19.371 --> 22:23.542
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:23.608 --> 22:24.910
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:24.976 --> 22:26.311
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:26.378 --> 22:27.679
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:27.746 --> 22:28.914
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line to take a pee ♪</i>

22:28.980 --> 22:30.382
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:30.449 --> 22:32.818
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:32.884 --> 22:35.420
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:35.487 --> 22:36.855
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
